{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Well, we were afraid to come out of there with the bayonets.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We're not talking just the gun but the stab them thing on the front there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we all got out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And my mother thought, now I'm going to be able to reciprocate to the Subitskis by making them safe from the Russians so they won't be treated like the rest of the German perpetrators.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That was the next danger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the first thing she had to establish was, how do we communicate with the Russians here to explain who we are, that we're-- that we're Jews left over.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "January '45.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In fact, Solzhenitsyn's army was in that very region, I read many years later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was very surprised.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we all came out of there staring at odd uniforms, odd gibberish, bayonets.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a very fortunate thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Russians were always very kind to children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the first thing they did was offer us-- and I don't know where they got this-- pieces of chicken.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother said, don't eat that, in German, this may be poisoned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we didn't eat it, but we were terribly hungry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they started pulling their sleeves up-- and I'm sure you may have heard this from other people-- uree, uree.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, that was close to the German word for Uhr, which is U-H-R, and they were trying to look for watches.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they had these watches strapped on their arms clear up to here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know how many you need to tell time, but that was loot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we gave them whatever we had.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "A couple of people maybe had a watch or two still.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "These were not people of that kind of means to begin with.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
